  "Question": "<p>How can we show that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_600\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"e^{-2\\lambda t}\\lambda^{2}\\leq\\frac{1}{e^{2}t^{2}}\\tag 1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mi>e</mi> <mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>\u03bb</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>t</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </msup> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mi>\u03bb</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>\u2264</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mn>1</mn> <mrow> <msup> <mi>e</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mi>t</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\tag</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> for all <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_601\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\lambda,t\\geq 0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>\u03bb</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>t</mi> </mrow> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span>?</p> <p>Applying <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_602\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\ln\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>ln</mi> </math></span> to both sides yields that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_603\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"(1)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </math></span> should be equivalent to <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_604\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"t\\lambda\\leq e^{t\\lambda-1}\\tag 2.\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>t</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>\u03bb</mi> </mrow> <mo>\u2264</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>e</mi> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>t</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>\u03bb</mi> </mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </msup> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\tag</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>.</mo> </mrow> </math></span> So, if I did no mistake, it should suffice to show <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_605\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x\\leq e^{x-1}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>\u2264</mo> <msup> <mi>e</mi> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>-</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> </math></span> for all <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_606\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x\\geq 0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span>. How can we do this?</p>",
